flannel /ˈflænəl/

(flannels) 

1. N-UNCOUNT Flannel is a soft cloth, usually made of cotton or wool, that is used for making clothes. 法兰绒 [oft N n] 

例： He wore a faded red flannel shirt. 他穿着一件褪了色的红色法兰绒衬衫。 

2. N-COUNT A flannel is a small cloth that you use for washing yourself. (洗澡擦身用的) 法兰绒布块 [英国英语]

